column1: "She's one of the survivors"?  How many people did he kill?  What Nassar did was horrible but he didn't kill anyone.  So why is the news trying to maximize how sensational this story is by using the term "survivor"?  The primary definition of survivor is someone who remains alive in an event where others have died.  So who did he kill?  If he didn't kill anyone then its ridiculous and shameful to call Aly a survivor.  Aly was sexually abused and she deserves justice but the fact that the media is using a word that doesn't fit just shows how shameful the news media is becoming with each passing day.  Everyone already hates Larry nassar.  its not necessary to use words out of context to make people hate him more because he is already one of the most hated people on earth.  Aly is NOT a survivor and shameful and disrespectful to people that are real survivors to call herself a survivor.  She was sexually abused so call her what she is.  A victim of sexual abuse.  But don't call her a survivor because as far as we know he never killed anyone.  She is not a survivor and it is shameful that she allowed people to coach her into saying that.
